	   <a name=96901804127924></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96901804127924><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>nice trick</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 15th 7:40 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2> OK, here is a nice trick to use when yo ucan no longer solo yellow cons. Im a 45 mage, Yellow cons are tough, even with a pet that has about 3000 hp. ok, herees the deal. DONT cast on the mob. Send in pet, make sure its buffed. Let pet solo mob till its down to around 30% health. Then type in /pet get lost (make sure you are close enough for pet to accept messages).&nbsp;&nbsp;then start casting to summon a new pet, when the spell is 1/4 of a bub from going off, hit enter. Pet suicides, 1 second later new one appears. THIS IS WHY YOU DONT CAST ON MOB. when The first pet dies, his aggro is wiped from the mob making you the target. BUT. if you dont cast on mob, he hits you once, pet jumps in , start over, Works very nicely.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
