<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=9786772971624></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9786772971624><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9786772971624>RE: nice trick</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9786772971624#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 5th 6:49 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is fairly common and since lots of stuff tend to get stated over again, it isnt necessarily to bring this back up.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am a lvl 51 High Elf Mage and will be working on a guide for this board as well but wont recommend it to the inexperienced player.  I use the tactic listed here even at 51 against just bout everything just because I dont hunt for xp.....I just come across stuff to kill to keep my pet busy.  =)  As far as downtime, it is non-existent.  I summon a pet and buff and send it ina nd sit there meddin while assistin back and forth between MoB and Pet......if Pet is doin fine I continue sitting but if the pet is losing I stand up...let the pet get to 20H and start castin another pet.....while the spell is castin I start typin /pet get lost....and the just a sec before the spell goes off I hit Enter.  Bout the time the one pet poofs another is beside me which I buff.  And since I am not patient and am not about to wait for my pet to regain all those HP (Earth Pet) if he is low, I kill him and summon another.  <br><br>Now the reason I choose this tactic is because I run a guild and enjoy the social aspects of the game more than the gain xp  gain xp  gain xp.....so while the pet is fightin, I am talkin!<br><br>And I gain just as much xp as someone who has to sit there and med bec they blasted the crap out of the last MoB and their pet finished the fight with 90H while their mana bar dropped to 40M.<br><br>Just some thoughts...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
